            <bug_when>2014-03-19 08:35:27 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>The website widgets offers special methods to add / remove event listeners. The reason why this is necessary are hard to get for a framework user. If its possible, we should remove these API and use the default on / off methods which would make it much clearer.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>39923</commentid>
            <who name="Daniel Wagner">daniel.wagner</who>
            <bug_when>2014-04-09 16:31:13 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>We determined that onWidget and offWidget are still necessary to prevent duplicate listeners and memory leaks. To make their purpose easier to understand, we added documentation and renamed the methods to $onFirstCollection and $offFirstCollection (with 1f2602b89c105ac8fde46060213d0ae411ab46e3 on master).</thetext>
